<br>
SoT is protected in their rotations by an agreement that we all honor.  When SOT breaks their agreement, we must consider ways to police our own server.  Therefore I suggest that we take action NOT as a form of 'getting back at SOT', not as revenge, but as simple justice.<br>
<br>
SoT is protected by rotations.  They use the rotation rules to their advantage when it suits them.  Since they choose not to honor fair play, the other guilds should work to bring them back into the flock through practicle measures.<br>
<br>
If our rotations and guidelines have no teeth, then there is nothing to stop SOT from acting as they do.  What I am proposing is simply that we show SoT the benefits of playing nice in the sandbox. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uwalvisstampede.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Walvis Stampede</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wog</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(3/23/02 4:29:31 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ameliare</span><hr size=1> I've only grouped with you a few times almost a year ago in lower guk, Trompen, but you were always a considerate and respectful player. Next time RF pops just shoot me a /tell and i'll be there to help.<br>
