<br>
This has nothing to do with whether or not the Ragefire list is accepted by The Rathe. Trompen was there along with Lenein at the time Ragefire popped. I spoke to Lenein the night before this took place regarding the Ragefire camp, and most people knew that Trompen has been holding the camp for a week. He <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> earned</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> the rights to that camp by spending days there. However, SoT chose to come into the zone and maliciously stole Ragefire from Trompen and his guild.  <br>
<br>
There is no way that SoT can make up for what they did. From the lack of response by their guild leadership it seems that they have no intentions of even attempting to make amends. Actions speak louder than words and the actions that SoT decided to take shows exactly what kind of guild it is. There may be many individual members that are part of SoT that are great people, but at this point it doesn't matter. The leadership of SoT has decided to show an utter lack of disrespect towards others on The Rathe so anyone who chooses to stay in that guild is condoning that choice and in fact deciding for themselves to embrace the reputation that SoT has earned for themselves. For those members that have stood up for what is right and has left the guild, I can only express my admiration for you in what I'm sure was a difficult decision. I too believe in guild pride and unity, but there is nothing to be proud of here no matter what excuses you come up with.   <br>
<br>
There are too many good guilds on The Rathe to let one poorly led guild ruin the fun for others. I can understand what Borick is trying to ask for, but I can not allow my guild to stoop to the level that SoT has although we have had our own incident with SoT that was...not pleasant. In the end, a guild's reputation is what matters the most and that is what makes a guild &quot;uber&quot; - not whether or not you can kill a mob in NToV or rush in on another guild's Fear Raid to kill Cazic Thule. I think the majority of people here can judge SoT for themselves and decide whether or not they have earned the right to be called &quot;uber&quot;. My own opinion is that not only is SoT not uber, the guild deserves no respect which in the end may be the punishment that they deserve. <br>
<br>
